comments.body:
A policy statement like this would grant access to AssumeRole

{code}
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": "sts:AssumeRole",
      "Resource": "arn:aws:iam::eucalyptus:role/eucalyptus/ResourceAdministrator"
    }
  ]
}
{code}

I've add this policy to an IAM user and when the user tries to "AssumeRole", a 403 Forbidden is returned:

{code}
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Action": "sts:AssumeRole",
      "Resource": "arn:aws:iam::eucalyptus:role/eucalyptus/ResourceAdministrator",
      "Effect": "Allow"
    }
  ]
}
{code}

I've verified that the console can issue AssumeRole, then substitute those credentials for making subsequent API calls.
I tried creating a volume after assuming the ResourceAdministrator role however, and got an error:
{code}
2015-10-28 11:59:15,544 boto [DEBUG]:<Response xmlns=""><Errors><Error><Code>UnauthorizedOperation</Code><Message>Not authorized to create: volume by user: arn:aws:euare::000141301794:user/admin</Message></Error></Errors><RequestID>bc92d974-515d-4e8c-9e5a-5c156066aea6</RequestID></Response>
{code}
